a-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jtc1665702704700.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jtc1665702704700.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jtc1665702704700.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jtc1665702704700\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Referential Integrity Management on MySQL\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__referential_integrity_management_on_mysql_161451\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Referential integrity is handled by Uniface.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__topic_d35747e1_d35748e1_d35749e1_d35750e1_d35751e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d795327e53\">\n                        \n Commit and Rollback\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54074e1_d54075e1_d54076e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> instructions are fully supported by MySQL Server, provided you use the correct storage engine.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54077e1_d54078e1_d54079e1\">Two-phase commit is not supported.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__topic_d35752e1_d35753e1_d35754e1_d35755e1_d35756e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d795327e71\">\n                        \n Locking\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54083e1_d54084e1_d54085e1\">All Uniface locking types are supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54086e1_d54087e1_d54088e1\">The default locking type is cautious. You can override cautious locking for individual entities by specifying optimistic locking in the entity definition in the application model.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__topic_d35757e1_d35758e1_d35759e1_d35760e1_d35761e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d795327e83\">\n                        \n read/lock\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__d6538e20\">You can specify paranoid locking by using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/lock</code> ProcScript command in the read trigger of an entity.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__topic_d35762e1_d35763e1_d35764e1_d35765e1_d35766e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d795327e98\">\n                        \n U_VERSION\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54098e1_d54099e1_d54100e1\">The MySQL connector supports the U_VERSION mechanism to improve locking performance. It is strongly recommended that you use U_VERSION, because this significantly reduces the chance of lock conflicts.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__topic_d35767e1_d35768e1_d35769e1_d35770e1_d35771e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d795327e108\">\n                        \n Transactions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtc1665702704700__p_d54104e1_d54105e1_d54106e1\">Transactions are started implicitly by MySQL when required.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Control</a><p>A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwe1665702704830.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>U_VERSION for Improving Locking Performance</a><p>Uniface supports a version mechanism which can improve performance by using a field called U_VERSION. U_VERSION is a one-byte field which you must assign to an entity for it to work. In other words, it is not automatically available.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529035\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529035\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Referential Integrity Management on MySQL Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Referential Integrity Management on MySQL Referential integrity is handled by Uniface. Commit and Rollback The commit and rollback instructions are fully supported by MySQL Server, provided you use the correct storage engine. Two-phase commit is not supported. Locking All Uniface locking types are supported. The default locking type is cautious. You can override cautious locking for individual entities by specifying optimistic locking in the entity definition in the application model. read/lock You can specify paranoid locking by using the read /lock ProcScript command in the read trigger of an entity. U_VERSION The MySQL connector supports the U_VERSION mechanism to improve locking performance. It is strongly recommended that you use U_VERSION, because this significantly reduces the chance of lock conflicts. Transactions Transactions are started implicitly by MySQL when required. Related Links Transaction Control A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction. U_VERSION for Improving Locking Performance Uniface supports a version mechanism which can improve performance by using a field called U_VERSION. U_VERSION is a one-byte field which you must assign to an entity for it to work. In other words, it is not automatically available. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}